This can include contact information, task lists, calendar, music library, and other personal and professional tools.
It’s similar to Google Drive, Microsoft Outlook, Slack, and Spotify all available in one browser and at the same time.
The peculiarity of the personal data storage facility is that the user can fully determine who can access what information.
The company calls this “personal empowerment with data”.
CEO John Bruce says the company’s idea is to bring together the resources, processes, and relevant skills that will enable access to the Solid platform for everyone.
The company currently consists of Berners-Lee, Bruce, a security platform purchased by IBM, some hired developers to work on the project, and a community of volunteer programmers.
